1
00:01:33,210 --> 00:01:38,850
[City of Romance]

2
00:01:39,250 --> 00:01:42,670
[Episode 20]

3
00:01:46,850 --> 00:01:48,810
The forecast says it's going to rain soon.

4
00:01:46,950 --> 00:01:53,590
[Episode 20: Ostrich Syndrome]

5
00:01:49,060 --> 00:01:50,410
Why don't I accompany you home?

6
00:01:50,970 --> 00:01:52,130
No need to trouble yourself.

7
00:01:52,160 --> 00:01:53,420
I can manage on my own.

8
00:01:56,630 --> 00:01:58,620
Can't you really stay a few more days?

9
00:01:59,229 --> 00:02:01,050
There are still so many places I haven't taken you to.

10
00:02:01,740 --> 00:02:03,050
It's not like we'll never see each other again.

11
00:02:03,500 --> 00:02:04,550
There will be other opportunities.

12
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:10,199
The car is here.

13
00:02:11,300 --> 00:02:12,750
How about I go back with you?

14
00:02:12,770 --> 00:02:14,230
I'll take you right to your doorstep.

15
00:02:14,250 --> 00:02:15,110
Then I'll come back.

16
00:02:15,440 --> 00:02:15,880
What do you think?

17
00:02:16,760 --> 00:02:18,600
It's hard to get tickets.

18
00:02:18,620 --> 00:02:20,410
I struggled for a while to get this one.

19
00:02:21,829 --> 00:02:22,600
Don't worry.

20
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:24,140
I'll call you when I get home.

21
00:02:25,900 --> 00:02:27,400
Alright, I'm off.

22
00:02:39,990 --> 00:02:41,960
I'll be going then.

23
00:02:47,760 --> 00:02:48,490
Well...

24
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:50,380
I'll wait here for you to come back.

25
00:02:51,680 --> 00:02:52,800
Just wait for me right here.

26
00:02:54,490 --> 00:02:54,990
Attention!

27
00:02:57,130 --> 00:02:58,130
Sir, let's go.

28
00:02:59,380 --> 00:02:59,990
Bye-bye.

29
00:03:00,220 --> 00:03:02,340
[Haixia Taxi; Passenger Onboard]

30
00:03:01,290 --> 00:03:02,210
Remember to think of me.

31
00:03:24,220 --> 00:03:24,850
So quick?

32
00:03:29,030 --> 00:03:29,730
Thank you.

33
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:30,670
Before the exam,

34
00:03:30,700 --> 00:03:32,150
I really owe it to this secret manual of yours.

35
00:03:32,470 --> 00:03:33,120
It's nothing.

36
00:03:38,520 --> 00:03:39,000
Here you go.

37
00:03:40,770 --> 00:03:42,090
The notes you asked to borrow the other day.

38
00:03:42,350 --> 00:03:43,040
Thank you.

39
00:03:43,440 --> 00:03:44,329
Well...

40
00:03:45,460 --> 00:03:46,940
It was raining heavily on that day in freshman year.

41
00:03:47,329 --> 00:03:49,440
My butt still hurts from that fall.

42
00:03:53,860 --> 00:03:54,950
I'm just kidding.

43
00:03:56,970 --> 00:03:57,870
Have a nice winter break.

44
00:03:58,010 --> 00:03:58,810
You too, have a nice winter break.

45
00:04:05,290 --> 00:04:06,230
Yu Shubo.

46
00:04:10,020 --> 00:04:10,800
Sister?

47
00:04:14,690 --> 00:04:16,740
Who was that girl just now?

48
00:04:16,950 --> 00:04:18,329
How come I haven't seen her before?

49
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:20,810
She was studying abroad before.

50
00:04:20,860 --> 00:04:21,630
We're classmates.

51
00:04:23,340 --> 00:04:25,290
So your relationship must be pretty good, right?

52
00:04:26,070 --> 00:04:26,910
It's okay.

53
00:04:27,960 --> 00:04:29,560
Okay.

54
00:04:31,870 --> 00:04:33,820
My brother has grown up.

55
00:04:34,150 --> 00:04:37,000
You're even taking the initiative to explain problems to others now.

56
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:40,020
Isn't it normal for classmates to explain problems to each other?

57
00:04:40,320 --> 00:04:41,790
You're such a prude.

58
00:04:43,030 --> 00:04:45,350
I heard that Su Yancheng finally beat the odds.

59
00:04:45,370 --> 00:04:46,150
He's in a relationship now.

60
00:04:46,880 --> 00:04:48,990
You're not bad-looking either,

61
00:04:49,020 --> 00:04:50,530
how come there's no news about you?

62
00:04:52,210 --> 00:04:54,430
Don't tell me you're...

63
00:04:54,890 --> 00:04:55,750
I am, sister.

64
00:04:56,500 --> 00:04:57,150
Really.

65
00:05:01,050 --> 00:05:01,880
I am.

66
00:05:01,910 --> 00:05:03,180
You're kidding me.

67
00:05:04,330 --> 00:05:05,060
Listen,

68
00:05:05,090 --> 00:05:06,660
you've grown up surrounded by women since you were little,

69
00:05:06,690 --> 00:05:08,010
and you're used to being a nice guy.

70
00:05:08,060 --> 00:05:09,790
But you can't be like that in a relationship.

71
00:05:09,930 --> 00:05:12,280
You need to give her a strong sense of security.

72
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:13,160
Got it?

73
00:05:14,680 --> 00:05:15,400
Got it.

74
00:05:16,260 --> 00:05:17,400
So,

75
00:05:17,870 --> 00:05:20,370
what's really going on between you and that girl just now?

76
00:05:50,130 --> 00:05:52,680
[Bai's Traditional Chinese Medicine Clinic]

77
00:05:56,140 --> 00:06:00,060
[Bai's Traditional Chinese Medicine Clinic]

78
00:06:08,380 --> 00:06:10,940
[Three years before it becomes a century-old store]

79
00:06:13,860 --> 00:06:14,880
I feel much better.

80
00:06:15,270 --> 00:06:16,030
Zhao,

81
00:06:16,140 --> 00:06:17,310
you still need to rest when you get back.

82
00:06:17,610 --> 00:06:17,920
Okay.

83
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:19,880
You know your third lumbar vertebra is quite swollen, right?

84
00:06:19,910 --> 00:06:20,590
Come on, get up.

85
00:06:24,490 --> 00:06:25,280
Alright, thanks.

86
00:06:25,280 --> 00:06:26,850
Remember to rest well when you get back.

87
00:06:26,870 --> 00:06:27,910
Sure, thanks, Bai.

88
00:06:27,940 --> 00:06:28,760
See you later.

89
00:06:33,180 --> 00:06:34,130
Take care.

90
00:06:48,550 --> 00:06:50,070
Still, my daughter gives the best massages.

91
00:06:50,760 --> 00:06:52,659
How did you guess it was me so quickly?

92
00:06:54,770 --> 00:06:56,700
Well, think about whose daughter you are.

93
00:06:57,159 --> 00:06:58,159
Bai.

94
00:06:58,190 --> 00:06:59,220
Bai, II.

95
00:06:59,680 --> 00:07:01,090
I've missed you so much.

96
00:07:01,110 --> 00:07:02,090
Let me take a look at you.

97
00:07:04,100 --> 00:07:05,130
Why are you wearing so little again?

98
00:07:05,430 --> 00:07:06,950
Our Man City is quite warm now.

99
00:07:07,060 --> 00:07:07,840
Sit down, let me check your pulse.

100
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:08,280
Alright.

101
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:09,670
Let me see

102
00:07:09,770 --> 00:07:11,550
whether you have been taking good care of yourself.

103
00:07:11,570 --> 00:07:12,730
Of course, go ahead.

104
00:07:16,100 --> 00:07:17,030
What's wrong?

105
00:07:17,700 --> 00:07:19,030
You have a boyfriend now?

106
00:07:19,890 --> 00:07:21,370
Don't be ridiculous.

107
00:07:22,050 --> 00:07:22,950
Let me see yours.

108
00:07:26,390 --> 00:07:27,820
Do I have a stepmother now?

109
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:30,160
You little rascal.

110
00:07:30,990 --> 00:07:31,650
Are you hungry?

111
00:07:31,860 --> 00:07:32,610
I'm starving.

112
00:07:32,640 --> 00:07:33,290
What do you want to eat?

113
00:07:33,360 --> 00:07:34,280
Tell me, I'll cook for you.

114
00:07:34,280 --> 00:07:36,520
I want to eat spare ribs,

115
00:07:36,540 --> 00:07:37,980
and shredded potatoes,

116
00:07:38,010 --> 00:07:38,770
and tomato and egg stir-fry...

117
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:39,280
Come on.

118
00:07:39,280 --> 00:07:39,980
Stop, stop, stop.

119
00:07:40,010 --> 00:07:40,700
Stop, stop, stop.

120
00:07:40,790 --> 00:07:42,100
Can you eat all that, you little glutton?

121
00:07:42,120 --> 00:07:43,250
My stomach is quite big.

122
00:07:43,530 --> 00:07:44,650
Alright, I'll make them for you.

123
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:45,240
Great!

124
00:07:45,380 --> 00:07:46,570
Wait, wait, wait.

125
00:07:48,420 --> 00:07:49,840
Your back still hurts, doesn't it?

126
00:07:49,940 --> 00:07:51,040
The same old problem.

127
00:07:58,710 --> 00:07:59,310
Mom,

128
00:08:00,220 --> 00:08:01,050
don't worry.

129
00:08:01,070 --> 00:08:02,450
Everything's fine at home.

130
00:08:03,390 --> 00:08:05,050
I'm doing great at school too.

131
00:08:05,110 --> 00:08:07,380
And I've made a lot of good friends.

132
00:08:07,410 --> 00:08:09,250
Wait, I'll tell you a secret in a moment.

133
00:08:10,040 --> 00:08:11,430
We can't let my father hear it.

134
00:08:14,430 --> 00:08:15,890
What secret are you telling your mom?

135
00:08:16,380 --> 00:08:17,620
I already said it's a secret.

136
00:08:17,650 --> 00:08:18,690
How could I tell you?

137
00:08:18,710 --> 00:08:19,530
Alright, alright.

138
00:08:20,720 --> 00:08:22,360
Look, our girl has grown up.

139
00:08:22,380 --> 00:08:24,170
Now she doesn't even tell me her secrets anymore.

140
00:08:24,190 --> 00:08:25,300
She got big wavy hair,

141
00:08:25,500 --> 00:08:26,620
and dyed it too.

142
00:08:26,740 --> 00:08:28,870
It's fashion, don't you understand?

143
00:08:31,040 --> 00:08:32,100
Don't worry.

144
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:34,309
Our daughter has grown up.

145
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:37,059
But I'll still take good care of her.

146
00:08:38,460 --> 00:08:39,620
Don't worry, Mom.

147
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:42,460
Who knows who'll be taking care of whom.

148
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:46,850
Your mom used to say the same thing.

149
00:08:48,060 --> 00:08:49,170
And then...

150
00:08:49,250 --> 00:08:50,720
Alright, alright, let's eat.

151
00:08:50,790 --> 00:08:51,580
Here you go again.

152
00:08:51,920 --> 00:08:52,830
Okay, okay, okay.

153
00:08:53,420 --> 00:08:54,710
You've made so much?

154
00:08:55,070 --> 00:08:57,670
Isn't it just six dishes and a soup?

155
00:08:57,690 --> 00:08:59,420
You've set quite a spread here.

156
00:08:59,440 --> 00:09:00,280
Are you going to eat or not?

157
00:09:00,570 --> 00:09:01,270
If you don't, I will.

158
00:09:01,490 --> 00:09:02,340
I will.

159
00:09:02,650 --> 00:09:03,350
Chopsticks.

160
00:09:03,670 --> 00:09:04,450
Over there.

161
00:09:05,820 --> 00:09:07,470
Whoever cooked it should finish it all.

162
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:08,140
Then don't touch anything.

163
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:09,000
This is all mine.

164
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:10,940
No way, I have to eat this chicken.

165
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:11,600
This one is for me to eat.

166
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:12,600
I also love these shredded potatoes.

167
00:09:16,490 --> 00:09:16,890
Here.

168
00:09:17,220 --> 00:09:17,980
It's so delicious.

169
00:09:19,170 --> 00:09:20,020
Let's talk.

170
00:09:20,210 --> 00:09:20,950
Talk about what?

171
00:09:22,180 --> 00:09:23,500
Talk about your boyfriend.

172
00:09:25,150 --> 00:09:27,310
Starting with such a pointed question right away?

173
00:09:27,370 --> 00:09:27,800
Yes.

174
00:09:28,770 --> 00:09:29,780
I don't have a boyfriend.

175
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:31,870
No boyfriend?

176
00:09:32,220 --> 00:09:34,210
Then what secret were you telling your mom earlier?

177
00:09:35,640 --> 00:09:37,170
I haven't asked you yet.

178
00:09:37,190 --> 00:09:39,160
Tell me, do you have a girlfriend now?

179
00:09:40,140 --> 00:09:40,840
Yes.

180
00:09:42,450 --> 00:09:43,410
Really? Is that true?

181
00:09:43,430 --> 00:09:45,670
It's true. How does it feel?

182
00:09:46,940 --> 00:09:48,050
I can't really describe it.

183
00:09:48,370 --> 00:09:50,040
A bit disappointed.

184
00:09:50,900 --> 00:09:52,280
A bit disappointed?

185
00:09:52,370 --> 00:09:53,600
You really have one?

186
00:09:54,770 --> 00:09:55,630
My girlfriend.

187
00:09:57,030 --> 00:09:58,310
Mom, I'm sorry.

188
00:09:58,330 --> 00:10:00,030
You're messing with me.

189
00:10:00,070 --> 00:10:01,800
You've been with my mom for years.

190
00:10:01,860 --> 00:10:03,810
You still want to dig a hole for me?

191
00:10:18,150 --> 00:10:18,800
Son,

192
00:10:19,250 --> 00:10:22,030
Mom needs to go on a business trip to Xue City for a few days.

193
00:10:22,210 --> 00:10:23,850
I should be back before the New Year.

194
00:10:24,090 --> 00:10:25,430
Take good care of yourself.

195
00:10:25,460 --> 00:10:26,680
Don't always eat takeout.

196
00:10:28,780 --> 00:10:29,540
I know.

197
00:10:38,070 --> 00:10:40,000
[Full of Wealth and Beauty]

198
00:10:38,100 --> 00:10:39,780
Xiaoduo, you've grown into a young lady.

199
00:10:39,880 --> 00:10:41,000
You're getting more and more beautiful.

200
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,360
Thank you, Uncle Wang. You probably couldn't recognize me, right?

201
00:10:43,450 --> 00:10:45,390
Well, whose daughter do you think she is?

202
00:10:46,170 --> 00:10:48,580
Yes, she came back to help as soon as the holiday started.

203
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:50,510
That's why we say you're so lucky, Bai.

204
00:10:51,980 --> 00:10:52,960
Xiaoduo,

205
00:10:53,290 --> 00:10:55,130
now that you're in college, have you started dating?

206
00:10:56,140 --> 00:10:57,100
What dating?

207
00:10:57,130 --> 00:10:58,770
Focus on her studies, that's what's important.

208
00:10:59,280 --> 00:11:00,340
Let me tell you,

209
00:11:00,480 --> 00:11:01,950
if any punk

210
00:11:01,980 --> 00:11:03,740
dares to have any funny ideas about my daughter,

211
00:11:03,760 --> 00:11:05,390
I'll break his legs.

212
00:11:05,730 --> 00:11:06,940
You old fuddy-duddy.

213
00:11:06,970 --> 00:11:08,450
This is called striking first to gain the upper hand.

214
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:10,640
Otherwise, all the good boys will be snatched up by others.

215
00:11:10,840 --> 00:11:11,530
Right?

216
00:11:11,620 --> 00:11:12,450
Exactly.

217
00:11:14,550 --> 00:11:15,560
What are you doing?

218
00:11:16,380 --> 00:11:18,700
Enjoying family time.

219
00:11:18,830 --> 00:11:20,660
Are you available to talk on the phone now?

220
00:11:20,770 --> 00:11:22,140
Yes, I am.

221
00:11:24,130 --> 00:11:25,020
Dad,

222
00:11:25,180 --> 00:11:26,490
I'll go upstairs first.

223
00:11:26,510 --> 00:11:27,230
I'm done.

224
00:11:27,250 --> 00:11:28,780
Goodbye, Uncle Wang and Uncle Shi.

225
00:11:29,100 --> 00:11:30,380
Who are you texting?

226
00:11:31,460 --> 00:11:34,460
No one. I'm... I'm going upstairs to study.

227
00:11:35,370 --> 00:11:37,240
It's vacation time, and you're still studying?

228
00:11:38,100 --> 00:11:39,120
Studious.

229
00:11:40,330 --> 00:11:41,370
Studious?

230
00:11:43,350 --> 00:11:45,630
Alright then. Uncle Wang, Uncle Shi, I'm heading upstairs.

231
00:11:45,650 --> 00:11:46,350
Okay.

232
00:11:48,570 --> 00:11:50,470
Are you texting a male or a female classmate?

233
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:17,280
Hello?

234
00:12:20,290 --> 00:12:20,800
Yeah.

235
00:12:21,620 --> 00:12:23,660
Do you know what my dad just said?

236
00:12:23,980 --> 00:12:25,790
He said if I dare to date,

237
00:12:25,840 --> 00:12:27,500
he'll break both our legs.

238
00:12:27,920 --> 00:12:29,080
Then I should start now

239
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:30,860
to practice running more,

240
00:12:31,150 --> 00:12:33,670
so we can run faster when the time comes.

241
00:12:33,940 --> 00:12:35,870
Remember to take me with you when you run.

242
00:12:36,650 --> 00:12:38,280
Of course I'll run with you.

243
00:12:39,370 --> 00:12:40,080
Wait a second.

244
00:12:40,560 --> 00:12:41,490
Come in.

245
00:12:44,070 --> 00:12:45,120
Studying, daughter?

246
00:12:46,780 --> 00:12:48,740
Well, carry on then.

247
00:12:48,970 --> 00:12:49,890
Are you okay?

248
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:55,490
Well, I was thinking...

249
00:12:55,520 --> 00:12:56,920
If you have some time,

250
00:12:57,080 --> 00:12:58,550
could you help Dad pick up a package?

251
00:12:58,850 --> 00:12:59,720
There are too many customers.

252
00:12:59,720 --> 00:13:00,360
I can't handle it all.

253
00:13:00,360 --> 00:13:01,770
A batch of towels I ordered has arrived.

254
00:13:01,840 --> 00:13:02,670
It's time to replace them anyway.

255
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:04,970
I'll go get them.

256
00:13:05,330 --> 00:13:05,850
Okay.

257
00:13:06,110 --> 00:13:06,740
Alright.

258
00:13:06,840 --> 00:13:07,420
Fine.

259
00:13:14,110 --> 00:13:16,000
My dad just came in. It scared me to death.

260
00:13:17,550 --> 00:13:18,880
My parents are on a business trip again.

261
00:13:21,030 --> 00:13:23,820
Then call me anytime.

262
00:13:24,130 --> 00:13:25,200
I'm always here.

263
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:27,100
How about I come over to see you?

264
00:13:28,670 --> 00:13:31,020
So your family is considered a traditional Chinese medicine dynasty?

265
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:31,990
I suppose so.

266
00:13:32,380 --> 00:13:33,410
It's been passed down for so many generations.

267
00:13:33,430 --> 00:13:35,390
So now you're doing that kind of...

268
00:13:35,580 --> 00:13:38,870
Chain traditional Chinese medicine therapy club, or...?

269
00:13:39,590 --> 00:13:40,040
Yes.

270
00:13:42,050 --> 00:13:45,060
Why don't you do more work at home?

271
00:13:45,220 --> 00:13:47,120
I'll be going back after the New Year anyway.

272
00:13:47,770 --> 00:13:48,430
Alright.

273
00:13:49,660 --> 00:13:50,920
Take good care of yourself.

274
00:13:51,510 --> 00:13:52,620
Remember to send me messages.

275
00:13:53,440 --> 00:13:54,000
Bye-bye.

276
00:13:54,760 --> 00:13:55,490
Good night.

277
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:57,260
You should rest early too.

278
00:13:59,200 --> 00:13:59,990
I miss you.

279
00:14:05,420 --> 00:14:06,920
About going abroad...

280
00:14:13,140 --> 00:14:15,240
[Chunchao Publishing House]

281
00:14:14,290 --> 00:14:15,230
Not bad.

282
00:14:15,590 --> 00:14:17,460
Your recent works have been quite good.

283
00:14:17,580 --> 00:14:19,810
And the update speed has improved as well.

284
00:14:20,130 --> 00:14:22,010
Have you found some secret formula?

